 LInk:https://github.com/InfoSecWarrior/Offensive-Payloads/blob/main/Html-Injection-Payloads.txt






                                                                                           CVSS Score


▶ Reflected HTML Injection | CVSS v3.1: 4.3 – Low | P4
   Stored HTML Injection | CVSS v3.1: 5.4 – Medium | P3



                                                                                           Impact


If HTML Injection exists, an attacker may:Alter page appearance (defacement)
                                          Display fake warnings or messages
                                          Inject phishing forms
                                          Mislead users into entering sensitive data
                                          Damage brand trust and reputation
                                          Assist further exploitation (XSS chaining)


                                           
                                                                                       Remediation


Sanitize all user inputs (server-side validation)
Encode output based on context (HTML encoding)
Use secure templating engines (auto-escaping)
Apply allowlists instead of blocklists
Avoid rendering raw user input in HTML
Perform security testing on all input points

✅ Best Practice:
Encode < > " ' & as: To &lt; &gt; &quot; &#x27; &amp;





   

